    "what_description": "Stelis simplex is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae. It is a terrestrial plant with a short stem, 1-2 cm long, and 2-3 linear, subulate leaves, 2-4 cm long, that arise from the base of the plant. The inflorescence is a raceme, 2-4 cm long, with 3-6 flowers. The flowers are resupinate, greenish-white to yellowish-green in color, with a long, narrow labellum that is almost as long as the sepals. The plant typically blooms in the summer months and is native to Central America.",
