    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Stelis simplex improperly include vomiting, diarrhea, nausea, abdominal pain and allergic reactions. These side effects are primarily due to the improper dosage and administration of the medication, which can lead to an imbalance of the chemical composition in the body. Vomiting, diarrhea and nausea are common gastrointestinal side effects, often caused by the sudden release of Stelis simplex into the system, overwhelming the body's natural digestive processes. Abdominal pain can occur due to the irritation of the stomach lining and intestines, while allergic reactions can range from mild skin rashes to life-threatening anaphylaxis, depending on the severity of the body's immune response. Overall, improper use of Stelis simplex can lead to a range of side effects, highlighting the importance of careful adherence to recommended dosages and administration guidelines.",
    "uses": "Stelis simplex has been traditionally used in folk medicine, although specific medicinal uses are not well-documented. Further research is needed to determine the full scope of its potential benefits. Some studies suggest that the plant may have anti-inflammatory properties. In addition, the plant's roots are sometimes used in traditional medicine in Latin America. More research is necessary to confirm the efficacy and safety of Stelis simplex for medicinal purposes.",
    "taxonomy": "Stelis simplex is classified as a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae. It belongs to the genus Stelis and is further classified as a member of the subtribe Pleurothallidinae. The subtribe Pleurothallidinae is a group of terrestrial orchids commonly known as \"pleurothallids.\" Stelis simplex is native to Central and South America and is characterized by its small, delicate flowers. The species is often found growing in shaded, humid environments.",
    "benefits": "Stelis simplex is a species of orchid, and while information on its specific health benefits is limited, some plants in the Stelis genus have been studied for their potential medicinal properties. Some research suggests that certain Stelis species may have antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and antioxidant effects. However, the specific health benefits of Stelis simplex are not well-documented. Further research is needed to fully understand the potential health benefits of this plant. It is essential to consult with a healthcare professional before using any plant-based remedies for medicinal purposes.",
    "parts": "Stelis simplex has been reported to have medicinal properties in some regions, although specific information on its traditional use and the parts used for medicinal purposes is limited. It is essential to note that the plant's medicinal properties have not been extensively scientifically studied and verified. The flowers and leaves of Stelis simplex are often used in folk medicine to treat various health conditions, but more research is required to confirm their efficacy and safety. In some parts of the world, Stelis simplex is used to make herbal remedies, but the specific parts used and their preparation methods vary widely. Further studies are needed to fully understand the medicinal properties and potential uses of Stelis simplex.",
    "intro": "Stelis simplex is a species of orchid native to the tropical forests of Central and South America, characterized by its small, delicate flowers and slender leaves. Traditionally, Stelis simplex has been used in folk medicine to treat various health issues, including fever, respiratory problems, and gastrointestinal disorders, due to its purported anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antiviral properties. The bioactive constituents of Stelis simplex include flavonoids, alkaloids, and phenolic acids, which are responsible for its medicinal activities. In herbal medicine, Stelis simplex is commonly prepared as a tea or tincture, and is often used to treat colds, flu, and other respiratory infections."
